# NFL Wire — Cursor AI Rules
# These rules are injected into every Cursor AI request automatically.
# Do not remove or modify section headers — Task Master depends on them.

## Project Overview
NFL Wire is a daily NFL team newsletter app supporting all 32 teams.
First active team: Seattle Seahawks.
Core philosophy: deliver a 5-minute morning briefing to the Commuter Fan persona.

## Tech Stack (Do Not Suggest Alternatives)
- Frontend: React + Vite + Tailwind CSS
- Backend: Supabase (PostgreSQL, Edge Functions, Auth)
- Deployment: Vercel
- Email: Resend (transactional email — do NOT suggest SendGrid, Mailgun, or nodemailer)
- AI Layer: Anthropic Claude API (claude-haiku-4-5-20251001 for summarization and relevance checks)
- Task Management: Task Master AI (MCP)

## File Structure
- src/components/        → React UI components
- src/pages/             → Page-level components (subscriber-facing)
- src/admin/             → Admin dashboard pages (protected)
- src/lib/               → Shared utilities, API clients, helpers
- src/hooks/             → Custom React hooks
- supabase/functions/    → Supabase Edge Functions
- supabase/migrations/   → SQL migration files
- .taskmaster/docs/      → PRD and project documentation
- .taskmaster/tasks/     → Task Master generated task files

## Code Style
- TypeScript for all files — never use plain JavaScript
- Strict mode enabled — no `any` types, use `unknown` or define explicit types
- Functional components only — no class components
- Named exports only — no default exports except for page components
- Always use async/await — never use .then() chains
- All async functions must have try/catch error handling
- Use 2 spaces for indentation
- Use double quotes for strings

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g. NewsletterPreview.tsx)
- Hooks: camelCase prefixed with "use" (e.g. useSubscriber.ts)
- Supabase Edge Functions: kebab-case (e.g. validate-source.ts)
- Database tables: snake_case (e.g. newsletter_metrics)
- Environment variables: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE

## Architecture Rules
- All Supabase queries go in src/lib/supabase/ — never inline in components
- All Anthropic API calls go in src/lib/ai/ — never call the API directly from components
- All Resend email calls go in supabase/functions/ — never from frontend
- Team-specific logic must always reference team_id — never hardcode a team name
- Global sources have team_id = null — always handle this case in queries

## Multi-Team Rules (Critical)
- Every query touching articles, sources, or newsletters MUST filter by team_id
- The pipeline iterates ALL active teams — never write single-team-only logic
- team_id is the single source of truth for all team-specific behavior
- Team colors, names, and slugs always come from the teams table — never hardcoded

## Supabase Edge Functions
- One function per concern: validate-source, run-content-pipeline, assemble-and-send
- Always handle errors gracefully — one team's failure must not crash the pipeline
- Log every significant operation with timestamp and team_id
- Use Supabase service role key for Edge Functions — never the anon key

## Anthropic API Usage
- Model: claude-haiku-4-5-20251001 for all summarization and relevance checks
- Always request JSON-only responses when parsing structured data
- Strip markdown backticks before parsing JSON responses
- Max tokens: 500 for summaries, 100 for relevance checks
- Always wrap API calls in try/catch — never let API failures crash the pipeline

## Email Template Rules
- Mobile-first — optimized for iOS Mail, Gmail, and Outlook
- Team primary_color and secondary_color always come from the teams table
- Four sections always present: Top Story, Quick Hits, Injury Report, Stat of the Day
- Footer always includes: 👍/👎 feedback, unsubscribe link, submit-a-source link
- Never inline styles that override team color variables

## Security Rules
- Never expose Anthropic API key to the frontend
- Never expose Supabase service role key to the frontend
- Admin routes (/admin/*) always require Supabase Auth with admin role check
- Always use parameterized queries — never string concatenation in SQL
- Sanitize all user-submitted source URLs before processing

## Task Master Workflow
- Before starting any task, run: task-master next
- After completing a task, update status: task-master set-status --id=X --status=done
- If a task is too complex, expand it: task-master expand --id=X
- Never skip tasks or work out of dependency order
- If requirements change, update tasks: task-master update --from=X --prompt="change description"

## Forbidden Patterns
- NO hardcoded team names, colors, or slugs anywhere in code
- NO direct fetch() calls to Anthropic API from React components
- NO .then() promise chains — always async/await
- NO var declarations — always const or let
- NO any TypeScript type — define proper types
- NO inline SQL strings — use Supabase query builder
- NO console.log in production code — use proper logging
- NO single-team assumptions — always design for 32 teams
